                {
                  "speaker_id": "",
                  "text": ". The physical toll of the trip is undeniable, but it's the mental weight that feels heaviest. Your hand rises to the pane. Five fingers spread against the glass.\n\nA Human in Equestria.\n\nIt's been a blur since you woke up in the Canterlot gardens. Princess Celestia was gracious enough to arrange this move to Ponyville, thinking a smaller town might be easier to adjust to than the capital. But as the train slows, the reality of your situation sets in.",
                  "type": "dialogue"
                },
                {
                  "speaker_id": "",
                  "text": "\nThe brakes squeal—a universal sound. You pull your collar up tight, hiding as much of your 'alien' features as you can. It's showtime.\n\nYou step out onto the platform. The air is fresh, smelling of hay and flowers. And everyone is a pony.",
